Edit: It won't let me post again, so I'll just have to see if I can edit in my response.  <br>
<br>
Rombus-<br>
<br>
Ok I'll retract that paragraph of my statement.  Saying that changing DoT's stun cap to 65 would be &quot;completely unbalancing&quot; is more than I should really say, and you're right in that its not a double barrel Telekin because one barrel would have a 0 sec stun duration.  I hadn't really been considering the duration of the stun, just the recast time.  <br>
<br>
They definitely shouldn't remove the stun component altogether since that would effectively screw over the folks who are using the spell in its current form (pvp'ers and folks hunting under 60 mobs for cash, xp,  faction, or any other reason).  <br>
<br>
Giving a lure based 0 recast stun would allow 1 wiz to do by himself what 2 or 3 wizzies can currently do with coordinated casts of Telekin (ie hold a mob spell-less to reject gating / chealing mobs).  Of course the 2 or 3 wizzies using Telekin wouldn't have the helpful lure component working to their advantage but they get to roll more resist checks.  I should have said that stopping gates and cheals on 60-64 mobs would be significantly easier for a lone wizard, but then again if it really matters that you stop them from gating or chealing you probably have more than 1 wiz around anyway and you're using coordinated Telekin's.  <br>
<br>
-Stencer<br>
